'''Tomáš Holeš''' (born 31 March 1993) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]], [[right-back]] or [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Czech First League|Fortuna Liga]] club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech national team]].<ref>{{Fotbal DNES|3011569}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Hradec Králové===
Before playing senior football, Holeš played in the youth league for Hradec Králové in 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Prokopec: Práce s tímto kolektivem má smysl|url=https://hradecky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/prokopec-prace-s-timto-kolektivem-ma-smysl20111214.html|website=[[Deník]]|publisher=Vltave Labe Media|date=14 December 2011|access-date=16 February 2024|language=cs}}</ref> He debuted at 18 years old in a [[Czech First League]] match against [[FC Slovan Liberec|Liberec]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Holeš prožil křest ohněm, hlídal slovenský expres|url=https://hradecky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/holes-prozil-krest-ohnem-hlidal-expres20120219.html|newspaper=Hradecký Deník|publisher=Vltave Labe Media|date=19 February 2012|access-date=16 February 2024|language=cs |last1=Tůma |first1=Jiří }}</ref> Holeš captained [[FC Hradec Králové|Hradec Králové]] during the 2016–17 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gól jsme dali po signálu, který se nepovedl, přiznal kapitán Hradce|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/tomas-holes-fotbal-hradec-kralove.A160822_2267912_fotbal_ten|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|date=22 August 2016|access-date=16 February 2024|language=cs}}</ref> Holeš started the 2017–18 season going into the final year of his contract with Hradec Králové, sitting out the traditional team photo at the start of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/domaci-souteze/hradec-fotbal-fotografovani-pred-sezonou.A170720_075455_fot_dsouteze_tof|title=Hradečtí se fotili před sezonou, Holeš s nimi na snímku už není|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=20 July 2017|access-date=16 February 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

===Later career===
After spending the second half of the [[2017–18 Czech First League]] on loan at [[FK Jablonec|Jablonec]], who he helped to Europa League qualification, Holeš joined Jablonec on a permanent transfer, signing a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Holeš zažil v Jablonci jaro snů a získal smlouvu na čtyři roky|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/tomas-holes-fotbal-jablonec.A180602_405451_fotbal_tof|author=Martin Sedlák|date=2 June 2018|access-date=16 February 2024|language=cs}}</ref> After a season at Jablonec he joined First League champions [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] in the summer of 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mistr posiluje. Slavia získala Hovorku s Holešem, Souček má novou smlouvu|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/slavia-praha-fotbal-zahajeni-letni-pripravy-2019-posily-odchody-tomas-holes-david-hovorka-tomas-souc.A190617_092752_fotbal_tof|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|date=17 June 2019|access-date=16 February 2024|language=cs}}</ref> On 6 January 2022, Holeš announced a new contract with Slavia Prague that will last until 2026.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tomáš Holeš prodloužil v Edenu smlouvu|url=https://www.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=Tomas-Holes-prodlouzil-v-Edenu-smlouvu-18970|publisher=SK Slavia Praha|date=6 January 2022|language=cs}}</ref>

==International career==
Having represented Czech Republic U21, Holeš debuted for the senior side in a [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] on 7 September 2020, playing the full 90 minutes as the Czech Republic lost 1–2.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Trojlístek vyhlíží premiérové starty v reprezentaci|url=https://hradecky.denik.cz/fotbal-zajimavosti/fotbal-reprezentace-crcesko-nominace-malinsky-holes-zeleny070920-hk.html|website=Deník|publisher=Vltave Labe Media|date=7 September 2020|language=cs}}</ref>

On 25 May 2021, Holeš was included in the final 26-man squad for the postponed [[UEFA Euro 2020]] tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Česká reprezentace oznámila nominaci na UEFA EURO 2020 {{!}} Reprezentace|url=https://repre.fotbal.cz/ceska-reprezentace-oznamila-nominaci-na-uefa-euro-2020/a14226|website=Czech Republic national football team|date=27 June 2021|language=cs}}</ref> On 27 June 2021, he scored the Czech Republic's first goal in the 68th minute and provided an assist for the second goal 12 minutes later in a 2–0 win over [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] to qualify for the UEFA Euro 2020 quarterfinals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Euro 2020, LIVE score updates: Netherlands vs Czech Republic Round of 16: Schick puts Czech 2-0 ahead against Netherlands|url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/euro/news/netherlands-vs-czech-republic-euro-2020-live-score-streaming-updates-blind-de-jong-schick-soucek/article35004045.ece|website=Sportstar|date=27 June 2021}}</ref>

